    "title": "Backend Developer 20260225",
    "description": "Role Summary: The Backend Developer will be responsible for creating and managing server-side components of web applications. They must possess a robust understanding of backend technologies to ensure efficient operations within the organization's digital infrastructure.\nKey Responsibilities: - Design, develop, deploy, maintain, and troubleshoot high performance backends that interact with user interfaces or external systems via API calls.\n- Implement security measures for database protection against cyber threats and ensure compliance with data privacy regulations such as GDPR.\n- Optimize queries to enhance the responsiveness of web applications, thereby improving customer experience. - Collaborate closely with DevOps team members to streamline release processes using continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) methodologies and containerization tools like Docker or Kubernetes.\nRequired Qualifications:\n- Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology, or a related field is required for consideration of the position; although not mandatory, professional certification such as Oracle Certified Professional Java SE Programmer can be an asset to your career growth within this company. - Proven experience with Python and Django framework preferred but not limited due to our commitment towards learning-friendly environment that encourages skill diversity.\nExperience Required: 0\u20131 years\nKey Skills: Python, Django, REST API development, PostgreSQL",
